\begin_layout Exercise
Over the course of this exercise,
 our goal is to calculate the integral
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\int\sqrt{1+x^{2}}\,\dl x.\label{eq:int1}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Calculate 
\begin_inset Formula $\int\sec(x)\,\dl x$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
This is a complicated integral by itself.
 You should use the 
\begin_inset Formula $u$
\end_inset

-substitution 
\begin_inset Formula $u=\sec x+\tan x$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Calculate 
\begin_inset Formula $\int\sec^{2}(x)\,\dl x$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
This one should be much easier.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Hint:
 Think through the trigonometric functions that you know.
 Does any of them have 
\begin_inset Formula $\sec^{2}(x)$
\end_inset

 as its derivative?
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "enu:item3"

\end_inset

